        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:1rem;color:#1e3a5f;">About WASA Faisalabad (FWASA)</h2>
        <p>Water and Sanitation Agency Faisalabad (FWASA) is the government authority responsible for water supply and sewerage management for <strong>Faisalabad city</strong> — Pakistan's third-largest city by population (12+ million) and the country's undisputed textile and industrial capital. FWASA operates under the Punjab government and supplies treated drinking water to millions of residential, commercial, and industrial consumers across Faisalabad district.</p>
        <p>Faisalabad's massive industrial sector — including textile mills, power looms, garment factories, and processing units concentrated in the SITE Industrial Area and other zones — creates one of Pakistan's highest industrial water demands. FWASA manages this alongside domestic consumer needs, making water supply management in Faisalabad a significant operational challenge.</p>
        <p>FWASA's online services are accessible at <strong>fwasa.com.pk</strong> — the official portal for bill inquiry, payment, complaint submission, and new connection applications. Monthly FWASA bills cover both water consumption charges and sewerage charges.</p>
